-- Regression: FIX-01 rank 14 — comptime signed int64_t arithmetic overflow.
--
-- **Motivating Incident.** Phase 65 audit row §5.9 (cross-referenced as top-20
-- rank 14) flagged src/comptime/comptime.c:410-412 — the comptime binop
-- evaluator used plain C signed arithmetic (`lv->as_int + rv->as_int`,
-- `lv->as_int - rv->as_int`, `lv->as_int * rv->as_int`) which is undefined
-- behavior on overflow under C11 6.5p5. Result: `comptime 9223372036854775807
-- + 1` could produce arbitrary results depending on optimizer mood —
-- wrap-around, optimized-away check, or trap — none of which is a
-- user-diagnosable error. Every Iron program that used comptime arithmetic
-- was one compiler upgrade away from silently changing semantics.
--
-- **Layout Diagram.** Pre-fix (comptime.c:410-412):
--     case IRON_TOK_PLUS:  return cval_int(ctx, lv->as_int + rv->as_int);
--     case IRON_TOK_MINUS: return cval_int(ctx, lv->as_int - rv->as_int);
--     case IRON_TOK_STAR:  return cval_int(ctx, lv->as_int * rv->as_int);
--
-- Post-fix:
--     case IRON_TOK_PLUS: {
--         int64_t result;
--         if (__builtin_add_overflow(lv->as_int, rv->as_int, &result)) {
--             emit_error(ctx, IRON_ERR_COMPTIME_ERROR, span,
--                        "comptime: integer overflow in addition");
--             return cval_null(ctx);
--         }
--         return cval_int(ctx, result);
--     }
-- (Same shape for IRON_TOK_MINUS via __builtin_sub_overflow and
--  IRON_TOK_STAR via __builtin_mul_overflow; division and modulo also
--  gained explicit INT64_MIN / -1 guards.)
--
-- **Fix Summary.** Phase 67-03 Task 1 rewrote the IRON_CVAL_INT binop switch
-- in src/comptime/comptime.c to use __builtin_add/sub/mul_overflow for +, -,
-- * and added explicit INT64_MIN / -1 checks for / and %. This fixture
-- exercises near-max arithmetic that MUST stay in range, proving the
-- non-overflow path still produces correct results after the rewrite. The
-- overflow diagnostic path is verified separately by a C-level unit of the
-- rewritten binop switch (direct error-code coverage via the negative
-- expected-value tests is blocked on run_integration.sh lacking a
-- .expected-error mode — see plan 67-03 Task 1 Step 3 for the rationale).
--
-- **Severity.** H — undefined behavior in comptime evaluator; optimizer
-- could silently change compilation semantics on upgrade.

val MAX_SAFE = comptime 4611686018427387900 + 7
val MIN_SAFE = comptime -4611686018427387900 - 7
val MUL_SAFE = comptime 1000000 * 1000000

func main() {
  println("max: {MAX_SAFE}")
  println("min: {MIN_SAFE}")
  println("mul: {MUL_SAFE}")
}
